.SH "NAME"
Mojolicious::Plugin::Charset \- Charset plugin
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.IX Header "SYNOPSIS"
.Vb 2
\&  # Mojolicious
\&  $app\->plugin(Charset => {charset => \*(AqShift_JIS\*(Aq});
\&
\&  # Mojolicious::Lite
\&  plugin Charset => {charset => \*(AqShift_JIS\*(Aq};
.Ve
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
Mojolicious::Plugin::Charset is a plugin to easily set the default charset
and encoding on all layers of Mojolicious.
.PP
The code of this plugin is a good example for learning to build new plugins,
you're welcome to fork it.
.PP
See \*(L"\s-1PLUGINS\*(R"\s0 in Mojolicious::Plugins for a list of plugins that are available
by default.
.SH "OPTIONS"
.IX Header "OPTIONS"
Mojolicious::Plugin::Charset supports the following options.
.SS "charset"
.IX Subsection "charset"
.Vb 2
\&  # Mojolicious::Lite
\&  plugin Charset => {charset => \*(AqShift_JIS\*(Aq};
.Ve
.PP
Application charset.
.SH "METHODS"
.IX Header "METHODS"
Mojolicious::Plugin::Charset inherits all methods from
Mojolicious::Plugin and implements the following new ones.
.SS "register"
.IX Subsection "register"
.Vb 1
\&  $plugin\->register(Mojolicious\->new, {charset => \*(AqShift_JIS\*(Aq});
.Ve
.PP
Register hook \*(L"before_dispatch\*(R" in Mojolicious in application and change a few
defaults.
